    "Id": "chassisdef_valedictus_VAL-9S",
    "Name": "Valedictus",
    "Details": "The Valedictus VAL-9S is a 95-ton Detroit Consolidated assault BattleMech introduced in 3151 for the Magistracy Armed Forces. Two Bombast Lasers, one in each arm, serve as primary weapons, delivering variable-output energy damage demanding skilled heat management from the pilot. Three Artemis IV-enhanced MML 7 launchers carry a diverse ammunition loadout including standard LRM and SRM rounds alongside Inferno and Swarm-I munitions, all protected by dual CASE II installations. A center-torso Laser AMS and head-mounted ER Small Laser complete the package.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Accurate Weapon - Missiles</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.17</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Upper, Right Upper</color>",
